macrozero.MacroZero.init.doc:
Initializes all I/O, Peripherals and anything else needed for the device to run

:return: Nothing

macrozero.MacroZero.run.doc:
Runs the interface. This function returns when PSO signals that device is shutting down.

Each loop and entry will be pulled off the Que and processed.

Based on events keyboards macros/display changes will take place.

:return: Nothing

macrozero.MacroZero.close.doc:
Closes all modules and resets I/0

:return: Nothing

macrozero.MacroZero.load_configuration.doc:
Try to load custom config file is present, if not present then try to load default config.

If default is not present then throw exception

:return: Nothing

macrozero.MacroZero.build_report_list.doc:
Build report_list for given command.

:param command: Command dictionary from config ex. Command = { "Type": "Keyboard Function" "Command": "Enter" :return report_list: list of reports needed to send command

modules.doc:
modules

Holds basic properties used by device

modules.RGBDriver.RGBDriver.build_output.doc:
Given the bank specified, generate the bit value based on the values in the output_mappings

:param bank: Specified bank you want to generate output bit value for :return: Value in bit format of specified bank

modules.RGBDriver.RGBDriver.set_output_m.doc:
Given a color and index set the associated color in RGB Rep Color has to be one of the supported color types, throw ValueError otherwise Index needs to be between 1-4, throw ValueError otherwise

:param color: color in COLOR_LIST :param index: int between 1-4 :return status: OK on success, error message on error case

modules.SSD1305.SSD1305.image.doc: Set buffer to value of Python Imaging Library image. The image should be in 1 bit mode and a size equal to the display size.

modules.SSD1305.SSD1305.set_contrast.doc: Sets the contrast of the display. Contrast should be a value between 0 and 255.

modules.SSD1305.SSD1305.dim.doc: Adjusts contrast to dim the display if dim is True, otherwise sets the contrast to normal brightness if dim is False.

modules.mkeyboard.MKeyboard.build_report.doc:
Generate byte report for given value

:param value: the value we want to convert into a report :return report: byte report for given value

modules.mkeyboard.MKeyboard.write_report.doc:
Writes key report to USB Device

First byte is modifier Second Byte is reserved, always = b"� Next 6 Bytes are scan codes, = b"� is no key press

:param report: a bytes :return:
